Sentencas: The present work aims to investigate the long-term stability of Ce/Co coated AISI 441 used as an interconnect material in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Long-term (4 year) degradation behavior of coated stainless steel 441 used for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Being a commercially available alloy the use of AISI 441 would greatly reduce the cost of SOFCs in comparison to tailor-made interconnect materials such as Crofer 22 APU.
Titulo: Long-term (4 year) degradation behavior of coated stainless steel 441 used for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: To analyze the long-term stability Ce/Co coated AISI 441 is exposed in air at 800 degrees C for up to 38 000 h. Mass gain values are recorded continuously.
Titulo: Long-term (4 year) degradation behavior of coated stainless steel 441 used for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: After 7 000, 23 000, and 35 000 h area specific resistance (ASR) measurements are performed, and cross-sections are prepared and analyzed using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and energy dispersive x-ray (EDX) spectroscopy.
Titulo: Long-term (4 year) degradation behavior of coated stainless steel 441 used for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Cr-evaporation measurements are conducted on samples exposed for up to 38 000 h.
Titulo: Long-term (4 year) degradation behavior of coated stainless steel 441 used for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications
